@Comment:	MOT does most of the talking , but both Mot and Chi seem to direct the activity equally. Mot , however , is more verbally directive. For the most part , MOT and Chi spend the time between two activities: moving the yellow wand by holding the balls above it and building a structure , which Mot refers to as <modern art> , on the black base. There is some discussion of which objects are magnets , and Mot notes that coins do not stick.
